===========================================================
Prerequisites for deploying application onto IoT Edge device
============================================================

Account: MSFT Azure Cloud account

Installation and setup on IoT Edge Machine: 
  Azure IoT Edge Runtime
  Intel® Distribution of OpenVINO™ Toolkit 
  Movidious Neural Compute Stick2 Drivers
  IoT Edge device connected to Azure IoT Hub

Operating System: Ubuntu 16.04

ToolKits: OpenVINO R3

Hardware:
  CPU: Intel(R) Core(TM) i3/i5/i7 
  VPU: Intel® Neural Compute Stick 2

System requirments:
  Memory: 16/32GB
  Storage: 12GB free space

Tested on below list of IoT Edge device(s):
   AAEON UP^2, IEI TANK, Intel NUC device

**System setup:
===============
  1. USB Camera connected to IoT Edge device
  2. Enabling xhost ($xhost +SI:localuser:root)
  3. Neural Compute Stick 2 plugged to IoT Edge device


Trobuleshooting:
================

  Container Create Options to mount NCS2 inside docker:

   {
    "HostConfig": {
        "Binds": [
            "/tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix",
            "/dev:/dev"
        ],
        "NetworkMode": "host",
        "IpcMode": "host",
        "Privileged": true
    },
    "NetworkingConfig": {
        "EndpointsConfig": {
            "host": {}
        }
    },
    "Env": [
        "DISPLAY=:0"
    ]
  } 

  How to: Once app is deployed follow below steps

  goto
   1. Azure IoT Hub on your portal.azure.com
   2. Select "IoT Edge" under "Automatic Device Managment"
   3. Select IoT device 
   4. Click "Set Modules"
   5. Click on Edge module w.r.t application deployed
   6. Select "Container Create Options" and past above code in there and click "Update"
   7. Finally "Review+Create"
   8. Restart your Edge module "sudo iotedge restart <module name>"

